''<h1>A DAY WITH MATILDA</h1>'' Today, Marco decided to stay at home, in smart-working, since his daugther Linda doesn't feel so well. Matilda is 5 years old, she's smart and loves to play with different things. Since he can't play with her, Marco has to find [[an interesting activity]] that Matilda can do during the day.Marco wants to find an activity that could involve but also amuse his daughter, he doesn't want her to watch all the time cartoons on tv. First of all, Marco asks to Matilda what she'd like to do; she wants to paint with watercolors or model something with DAS. She can't do these activities alone, so Marco decides to [[search on the web]] something that can recall them. He is searching for: [[an educational activity]] [[a funny and interactive activity]]The web is full of virtual educational activities. Though, there may be the risk that they are too briefs, too complicated or even boring for a five years old child. Marco tries to [[search something in a more definite way]], maybe specifying the topic or the kind of activity. Without a more educational scope, the risk is that Matilda is immediately bored by the activity; Maybe it can be useful searching for something with a more attractive topic. Since Matilda loves animals, looking for [[virtual interactive resources having as topic the animal]] could be a good idea.Matilda, since she's born, has had a special connection with animals. They even have a cat, Birillo, and Matilda is extremely fond of him; unfortunately, it's been 5 days that they don't see him, Matilda miss him a lot and she still hopes that he will come back. Marco decides to search about... [[a virtual place where to publish missing animals posters]] [[virtual interactive resources having as topic the animal]]A good activity for Linda could be to design a missing poster with some simple graphic editor (like paint) and then upload it on a virtual space. They just have to find [[the right web space]].A site grabs Marco's attention: 'Wanted!', a virtual, interactive space for you and your animal. While deepening, Marco found a lot of interesting activities that Matilda can do on this site, like a virtual visit with a personalised guide. After have set all, Marco lets [[Matilda begins her visit]].Marco finds this webspace, 'Wanted!', that allows you to publish an announce to find your pet but also material of any kind (a video, a text, a collection of images etc...) to talk about it. So Marco decides to let Matilda [[realize a missing poster for Birillo]]; then, she can find her favourite photos or videos about Birillo, and write something about him, to let the people know its history by uploading [[all on the site]].After have choosing her guide (that she based on the aspect of her cat, Birillo) she starts [[the visit through the virtual rooms]]. <img
